<p>The mother-of-two announced their second pregnancy back in June, showing off her baby bump in the video for her single Wake Up Love. </p>

<p>She wrote on Instagram: 'To our girls, the name father is another name for what we created, love. I have a King to uphold and Queens to raise. #ourblackmenmatter #ourblackwomenmatter #ourblackkidsmatter.'</p>

<p>Taylor told People at the time: 'We're ready, and we're very excited. Iman is super excited. Junie is ecstatic — I'm talking super ecstatic. Everybody is just excited. I can't wait. I've got three more months left until we meet our little princess.'</p>

<p>She added of Junie's excitement: 'Kids handle siblings differently. You have kids that are a little bit jealous. But she's so excited and preparing herself to be a big sister. </p>

